block layout-content
  // Breadcrumb Navigation
  nav.bg-light.py-2(aria-label='breadcrumb')
    .container
      ol.breadcrumb.mb-0
        li.breadcrumb-item
          a.text-decoration-none(href='/') Home
        li.breadcrumb-item
          a.text-decoration-none(href='/articles') Articles
        li.breadcrumb-item.active(aria-current='page') From README to Reality

  // Hero Section
  section.bg-gradient-primary.py-5
    .container
      .row.align-items-center
        .col-lg-10.mx-auto.text-center
          h1.display-4.fw-bold.mb-3
            i.bi.bi-file-earmark-text.me-3
            | From README to Reality
          h2.h3.mb-4 Teaching an Agent to Bootstrap a UI Theme with Markdown and NuGet
          p.lead.mb-5
            | What happens when a smart editor reads your README like an executable script?
            | I tested that question by writing a NuGet package that configures itself—just from markdown.
            | This is the story of how documentation became automation.

  // Main Article Content
  article#main-article
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-8.mx-auto
          // Article Metadata
          header.mb-4
            .article-meta.text-muted.mb-3.pb-3.border-bottom
              time(datetime=publishedDate) #{new Date(publishedDate).toLocaleDateString('en-US', {year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric'})}
              span.mx-2 •
              span by #{pageAuthor}
              span.mx-2 •
              span #{estimatedReadTime} min read

          // Introduction
          section.mb-5
            h2.h3.mb-4
              i.bi.bi-lightbulb.me-2
              | The Lightbulb Moment
            p.mb-4
              | While using Visual Studio Code in agent mode, I pointed it to a NuGet package with a detailed README.
              | It didn't just highlight it—it followed it. It installed the package, registered the services,
              | updated my <code>Program.cs</code>, and made everything work without a manual step.
              | That was the moment I realized:

            blockquote.blockquote.text-center.bg-light.p-4.rounded
              p.mb-0.fs-5.text-primary.fw-bold
                | A well-written README isn't documentation. It's an interface for automation.

          // GitHub Copilot Agent Mode Section
          section#agent-mode.mb-5
            .card.shadow-sm.border-primary
              .card-header.bg-primary.text-white
                h3.card-title.mb-0
                  i.bi.bi-robot.me-2
                  | What Is GitHub Copilot Agent Mode?
              .card-body
                p.mb-4
                  | GitHub Copilot's agent mode empowers users to delegate complex tasks to the AI,
                  | offering a more autonomous and interactive development experience. It allows
                  | Copilot to analyze code, plan changes, execute commands, and even iterate on
                  | its output to achieve a desired result.

                h4.text-primary.mb-3 Key Features and Capabilities:
                .row.g-3.mb-4
                  .col-md-6
                    .card.h-100.border-info
                      .card-body
                        h6.card-title
                          i.bi.bi-gear.text-info.me-2
                          | Autonomous Development
                        p.card-text.small Execute code edits, commands, and planning from high-level prompts.
                  .col-md-6
                    .card.h-100.border-success
                      .card-body
                        h6.card-title
                          i.bi.bi-arrow-repeat.text-success.me-2
                          | Iteration and Self-Healing
                        p.card-text.small Identify, fix, and improve code autonomously.
                  .col-md-6
                    .card.h-100.border-warning
                      .card-body
                        h6.card-title
                          i.bi.bi-search.text-warning.me-2
                          | Codebase Analysis
                        p.card-text.small Understands context and navigates project files.
                  .col-md-6
                    .card.h-100.border-danger
                      .card-body
                        h6.card-title
                          i.bi.bi-tools.text-danger.me-2
                          | Tool Integration
                        p.card-text.small Supports build/test/run tasks via tools.

                h4.text-primary.mb-3 How to Use It:
                ol.list-group.list-group-numbered.list-group-flush.mb-4
                  li.list-group-item.border-0 Enable Agent Mode in VS Code under Tools > Options > GitHub > Copilot.
                  li.list-group-item.border-0 In the Copilot Chat window, select "Ask", then switch mode to "Agent".
                  li.list-group-item.border-0 Enter a high-level prompt.
                  li.list-group-item.border-0 Review suggestions and iterate.
                  li.list-group-item.border-0 Confirm terminal/tool invocations when prompted.

                .alert.alert-success
                  h5.alert-heading
                    i.bi.bi-trophy.me-2
                    | Benefits
                  ul.mb-0
                    li Increased productivity through automation
                    li Faster development cycles
                    li Improved code quality with automatic fixes
                    li Enhanced onboarding and collaboration for teams

          // Turning Idea into Action
          section#project-overview.mb-5
            h2.h3.mb-4
              i.bi.bi-rocket.me-2
              | Turning Idea into Action
            p.mb-4
              | I set out to prove this could work with something practical. I created
              a.text-decoration-none(href="https://www.nuget.org/packages/WebSpark.Bootswatch/" target="_blank" rel="noopener") WebSpark.Bootswatch
              | , a NuGet package that simplifies adding
              a.text-decoration-none(href="https://bootswatch.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener") Bootswatch themes
              |  to ASP.NET projects.

            p.mb-4
              | The goal was to let any developer (or smart agent) style a site with one command
              | and a few configuration lines—no asset downloads, no layout hacks.

            .card.bg-light.mb-4
              .card-body
                h4.mb-3
                  i.bi.bi-check-circle.text-success.me-2
                  | What It Does
                ul.list-unstyled.mb-0
                  li.mb-2
                    i.bi.bi-check2.text-success.me-2
                    | Adds SCSS support and all Bootswatch themes via CDN
                  li.mb-2
                    i.bi.bi-check2.text-success.me-2
                    | Integrates with your layout file for theme switching
                  li.mb-2
                    i.bi.bi-check2.text-success.me-2
                    | Provides dynamic theme routing
                  li
                    i.bi.bi-check2.text-success.me-2
                    | Plays nicely with Vite, PrismJS, and modern dev tooling

          // Code Sample Section
          section#installation.mb-5
            h2.h3.mb-4
              i.bi.bi-code-slash.me-2
              | Code Sample: Installation
            p.mb-4 Here's how easy it is to get started with the package:

            .row.g-4.mb-4
              .col-md-6
                .card.h-100
                  .card-header.bg-dark.text-white
                    h5.mb-0
                      i.bi.bi-terminal.me-2
                      | Package Installation
                  .card-body.p-0
                    pre.language-bash.mb-0
                      code.language-bash.
                        dotnet add package WebSpark.Bootswatch

              .col-md-6
                .card.h-100
                  .card-header.bg-primary.text-white
                    h5.mb-0
                      i.bi.bi-file-earmark-code.me-2
                      | Service Registration
                  .card-body.p-0
                    pre.language-csharp.mb-0
                      code.language-csharp.
                        // In Program.cs
                        builder.Services.AddBootswatch();

          // Live Demo Section
          section#demo.mb-5
            .card.text-center.border-success
              .card-body.py-5
                i.bi.bi-laptop.display-4.text-success.mb-3
                h3.card-title Live Demo
                p.card-text.mb-4 Want to see it in action? Visit the live demo site to explore different Bootswatch themes.
                a.btn.btn-success.btn-lg(href='https://bootswatch.markhazleton.com/' target='_blank' rel="noopener")
                  i.bi.bi-box-arrow-up-ne.me-2
                  | Bootswatch Demo Site

          // Why This Matters Section
          section#significance.mb-5
            h2.h3.mb-4
              i.bi.bi-lightbulb-fill.me-2
              | Why This Matters
            p.mb-4
              | This is more than packaging styles—it's about writing installation instructions
              | that an AI agent can understand and execute. Instead of codegen or scaffolding,
              | you're giving the system a blueprint.

            .row.g-4.mb-4
              .col-md-4
                .card.h-100.text-center.border-primary
                  .card-body
                    i.bi.bi-plugin.display-4.text-primary.mb-3
                    h5.card-title No Custom Plugins
                    p.card-text.small No need for custom plugins or extensions
              .col-md-4
                .card.h-100.text-center.border-success
                  .card-body
                    i.bi.bi-file-earmark-text.display-4.text-success.mb-3
                    h5.card-title README as Script
                    p.card-text.small The README becomes your install script
              .col-md-4
                .card.h-100.text-center.border-info
                  .card-body
                    i.bi.bi-box.display-4.text-info.mb-3
                    h5.card-title Self-Deploying Module
                    p.card-text.small The NuGet package becomes a self-deploying module

          // GitHub Repo Section
          section#github.mb-5
            .card.border-dark
              .card-header.bg-dark.text-white
                h3.card-title.mb-0
                  i.bi.bi-github.me-2
                  | The GitHub Repository
              .card-body
                p.mb-3
                  | Full source, examples, and README are available on GitHub.
                  | The repository demonstrates the complete implementation and provides
                  | detailed documentation for both human and AI consumption.
                a.btn.btn-dark(href="https://github.com/MarkHazleton/WebSpark.Bootswatch" target="_blank" rel="noopener")
                  i.bi.bi-github.me-2
                  | View on GitHub

          // Conclusion
          section.mb-5
            .card.bg-dark.text-white
              .card-body.py-5
                h2.h3.mb-4.text-center
                  i.bi.bi-chat-quote.text-warning.me-2
                  | Final Thoughts

                p.lead.text-center.mb-4
                  | This project changed how I write READMEs. I now structure them as if they're
                  | going to be parsed by someone—or something—that can act on them.

                blockquote.blockquote
                  p.mb-3.fs-5
                    | "It's a lightweight, flexible way to guide both human and machine through the installation process."
                  p.mb-3.fs-5
                    | In an age of AI-assisted development,
                    cite(title="Source Title") the best interface might just be your documentation

        .col-lg-4
          aside.sticky-top
            // Table of Contents
            nav.mb-4(aria-label='Table of Contents')
              .card.shadow-sm
                .card-header.bg-primary.text-white
                  h3.card-title.mb-0
                    i.bi.bi-list-ul.me-2
                    | Table of Contents
                .card-body
                  ol.list-group.list-group-numbered.list-group-flush
                    li.list-group-item.border-0.ps-0
                      a.text-decoration-none(href='#agent-mode') GitHub Copilot Agent Mode
                    li.list-group-item.border-0.ps-0
                      a.text-decoration-none(href='#project-overview') Project Overview
                    li.list-group-item.border-0.ps-0
                      a.text-decoration-none(href='#installation') Installation Guide
                    li.list-group-item.border-0.ps-0
                      a.text-decoration-none(href='#demo') Live Demo
                    li.list-group-item.border-0.ps-0
                      a.text-decoration-none(href='#significance') Why This Matters
                    li.list-group-item.border-0.ps-0
                      a.text-decoration-none(href='#github') GitHub Repository

            // Quick Links
            .card.shadow-sm.mb-4
              .card-header.bg-success.text-white
                h5.mb-0
                  i.bi.bi-link-45deg.me-2
                  | Quick Links
              .card-body
                ul.list-unstyled.mb-0
                  li.mb-2
                    i.bi.bi-box.text-primary.me-2
                    a.text-decoration-none(href="https://www.nuget.org/packages/WebSpark.Bootswatch/" target="_blank" rel="noopener") WebSpark.Bootswatch NuGet
                  li.mb-2
                    i.bi.bi-laptop.text-success.me-2
                    a.text-decoration-none(href="https://bootswatch.markhazleton.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener") Live Demo Site
                  li.mb-2
                    i.bi.bi-github.text-dark.me-2
                    a.text-decoration-none(href="https://github.com/MarkHazleton/WebSpark.Bootswatch" target="_blank" rel="noopener") GitHub Repository
                  li
                    i.bi.bi-palette.text-info.me-2
                    a.text-decoration-none(href="https://bootswatch.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener") Bootswatch Themes

            // Technology Stack
            .card.shadow-sm.mb-4
              .card-header.bg-info.text-white
                h5.mb-0
                  i.bi.bi-stack.me-2
                  | Technology Stack
              .card-body
                .d-flex.flex-wrap.gap-2
                  span.badge.bg-primary.text-white NuGet
                  span.badge.bg-secondary.text-white ASP.NET Core
                  span.badge.bg-success.text-white Bootstrap
